Sometimes, we want to perform a whole range of actions on a piece of data.<br/>
Say e.g we have an alphanumeric string, we want to extract all the digits from it, get all the prime numbers, double each of those numbers and then sum the result.<br/>
That entire workflow could look something like this (trivial example):
```javascript
function split(str){ return str.split('');}
function isPrime(num) { //prime calc here -  return true|false };
function filterPrime(...arr) { return arr.filter(isPrime);};
function double(num) { return num * 2};
function doubleArr(...arr) { return arr.map(double);};
function sum(a,b){ return a + b;};
function sumArray(...arr) { return arr.reduce(sum);}

var sum = sumArray(doubleArray(filterPrime(split('123abc4d56;;q78910'))));
```
After completing this kata, you will be able to rewrite that code to look like this:
```javascript
var sum = split.then(filterPrime).then(doubleArray).then(sumArray)('123abc4d56;;q78910');
```

See test cases for more examples.
